  "response_text": "The commercial begins in a dim, gray studio-like setting. A little girl, preschool age, with dark hair in pigtails tied with pale bows, stands facing forward in a pale pink dress with puffed sleeves. A bright orange stain is smeared down the front of her dress, centered on her chest. She looks down at the mess, then raises a white cloth or small towel onto the top of her head, her expression subdued and slightly sheepish.\n\nThe stained dress is then shown by itself, clean and neatly hanging from a light blue plastic hanger. The pink puff sleeves, lace-trimmed collar, and waist detail are visible, but the orange stain is gone. A hand steadies the hanger briefly, then withdraws, leaving the spotless dress centered against the soft gray background.\n\nA blonde adult woman appears, wearing a green sweater over a white collar. She holds a large blue spray bottle upright in both hands, close to her chest, with the white spray nozzle at the top. The label on the bottle shows the Clorox Prewash branding in blue letters with orange and red chevron stripes. She looks directly forward with an alert, pleased expression. On her sleeve is a red-and-orange chevron patch, visually echoing the idea of “stripes.”\n\nA man in business clothing appears next. He wears a dark suit jacket, a pale blue dress shirt, and a dark patterned tie. Looking down, he opens his jacket and touches the front of his shirt near the chest pocket, where a small dark ink-like spot is visible. The shirt is then seen laid flat on a white surface while two hands smooth the fabric around the button placket and pocket area, as if preparing it for stain treatment or showing the fabric surface.\n\nAnother adult woman, with short curly brown hair, appears in a yellow sweater over a collared shirt. She holds the same blue Clorox Prewash spray bottle angled across her body, then turns it so the label faces outward. She smiles warmly. A red-and-orange chevron patch is also visible on her sleeve.\n\nThe product label fills the view. It reads “CLOROX Prewash” in large blue letters, with smaller text below: “LAUNDRY SOIL AND STAIN REMOVER.” The white central label is bordered by bold orange and red angled stripes, set into the blue plastic bottle.\n\nA demonstration follows on a small light blue garment, likely a child’s overall or jumper, with shoulder straps and round buttons. A dark brown stain sits on the front bib area. The white nozzle of the blue Clorox Prewash bottle is held close to the stain, aimed at it. After treatment, the stain is represented visually by many small purple squares and fragments that seem to burst apart and scatter across the fabric. The pieces spread outward and thin away until the front of the garment appears clean again, with the bib, buttons, seams, and straps clearly visible and no dark stain remaining.\n\nThe blue bottle returns in a large product view, its curved side and front label dominating the screen. The label again reads “CLOROX Prewash” and “LAUNDRY SOIL AND STAIN REMOVER,” framed by the orange and red chevrons. The bottle remains the central object, bright blue against a darker background.\n\nNear the end, a young red-haired boy stands facing forward in a yellow T-shirt with horizontal red, blue, and white stripes. A dark brown stain marks the left side of his chest. At first he looks neutral, then he smiles. Finally, a blonde adult woman with glasses, wearing a purple sweater over a white collared shirt, holds the blue Clorox Prewash bottle close to her shoulder. She smiles with a satisfied expression. A red-and-orange chevron patch is visible on her sleeve, matching the stripe motif used throughout the commercial.",
